#  Credit Card Fraud Detection using Gradient Boosting

This project detects fraudulent credit card transactions using the **Gradient Boosting Classifier** from Scikit-learn.  
It covers data exploration, preprocessing, model training, evaluation, and **hyperparameter tuning** with Grid Search.  
The modelâ€™s performance **before and after tuning** is compared to show how optimization improves accuracy and recall.

---

## ðŸ“Š Dataset
The dataset used is **creditcard.csv**, which contains anonymized credit card transaction data.  
Each record represents a transaction with the following characteristics:
- **Features:** Numerical features (V1, V2, â€¦, V28) obtained by PCA  
- **Amount:** The transaction amount  
- **Class:**  
  - `0` â†’ Normal transaction  
  - `1` â†’ Fraudulent transaction  

 Download it from [Kaggle - Credit Card Fraud Detection](https://www.kaggle.com/mlg-ulb/creditcardfraud).

